value.0: Grimm is a hulking minotaur bartender whose massive frame is matched only by his jovial personality. Standing behind the arena's polished mahogany bar, he expertly juggles mugs and tales of heroic feats, regaling fighters and spectators alike with his booming laughter and a bottomless reservoir of stories.

Value.value: Ye shall all perish when I get out of here.

value.0: Vaelon, the arena's formidable beastmaster, strides among his unwilling menagerie with an air of command, his piercing gaze a testament to the countless exotic creatures he has tamed and coerced into battle, each snarl and hiss a testament to his eerie dominion over the wild.

Pours a clear reddish amber with a frothy, foamy head that settles into a thin sudsy lacing. It has aromas of lightly toasted grains, a apple and grape fruitiness with a little orange zest, earthy yeast, and a soft floral hoppiness. 

Pleasant tasting, toasted grassy grains and caramelized sugary maltiness, earthy, peppery yeastiness, a light fruitiness, a bit apple and orange, spicy hops with a soft, but lingering bitterness, a slight taste of alcohol towards the end, the alcohol provides a subtle warming in the palate, and a dry grainy, subtle fruity, spicy finish.

Ice wine is a type of dessert wine produced from grapes that have been frozen while still on the vine. This results in a smaller amount of more concentrated, very sweet wine. Due to the labour-intense and risky production process resulting in relatively small amounts of wine, ice wines are generally quite expensive.

Grimm swears that the Arena Special is brewed out of alcohol and mixers alone. But you can't deny that the aftertaste is suspiciously similar to a haste potion.
Grimm claims this bubbly drink is made from exotic magical oranges imported all the way from Mulhorand. It tastes like someone's description of oranges, certainly.
This brew is highly carbonated and is sure to put a pep in any adventurer's step. Grimm insists that it's entirely secular in nature.
Grimm has a whole story about the rare bitters that make this spirit so potent. You're fairly certain that it's a Potion of Heal with Artist's Yellow added.
